      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the biological fusion mass; yield force defines onset of permanent deformation leading to loss of fixation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield structural reserve. All three QoIs map directly to FDA guidance on spinal implant mechanical performance and ASTM F1717 acceptance criteria."
