    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the conservative nature of the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol and the strong quantitative agreement across all QoIs (maximum E/uval 1.62, maximum percent difference 8.1%). The overall evidence package provides sufficient confidence for regulatory submission supporting the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
